      "name": "Shai-Hulud v2 NPM Supply Chain Attack",
      "description": "A campaign beginning in late November 2025 involving the compromise of numerous npm packages (including those from Zapier, ENS Domains, PostHog, and Postman) to distribute the Shai-Hulud malware. The campaign resulted in mass exfiltration of secrets, creation of over 22,000 public GitHub repositories, and destructive actions on infected hosts.",
